 `BCDHPublicKey.readObject` indirectly using a custom serialization method instead of `ObjectInputStream.readOrdinaryObject`, but that doesn't seem possible. I’m considering whether a JDK serialization filter could help, but again, it seems like that won't work.\\n\\nMaybe I can explore native reflection registration using the `@RegisterForReflection` annotation from the GraalVM library. I’m going to need to check if there are any dependencies for that since they might not be included in the tests right now. I'll have to do some searching!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1pjZSinGJc7Ki7OBc8cDJoo6|fc_0132cd3bb2a1a7a70169fbcb34b7c08195a9757a4b3b38aed3", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"@RegisterForReflection|RegisterForReflection|SerializationFeature|Object.class\" tests/src/*/*/*/src/test/java -S | head -100", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3055, "output": 528, "cacheRead": 58880, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 62463, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778109223164, "responseId": "resp_0132cd3bb2a1a7a70169fbcb27d8f881958dbeaabcb6395edb"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_1pjZSinGJc7Ki7OBc8cDJoo6|fc_0132cd3bb2a1a7a70169fbcb34b7c08195a9757a4b3b38aed3", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/com.google.auto.value/auto-value-annotations/1.10/src/test/java/com_google_auto_value/auto_value_annotations/Auto_value_annotationsTest.java:112:        assertThat(autoBuilderWildcard.getUpperBounds()).containsExactly(Object.class);\ntests/src/com.google.auto.value/auto-value-annotations/1.10/src/test/java/com_google_auto_value/auto_value_annotations/Auto_value_annotationsTest.java:122:        assertThat(enumArgumentWildcard.getUpperBounds()).containsExactly(Object.class);\ntests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jsr310/2.13.1/src/